                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    In this day and age it should be easy to know how and what to eat but people still struggle because of all the bad information out there. There are plenty of good resources though, and most are in agreement that eating natural food,
                                    in smaller portions, more regularly with plenty of water, is the best way.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    In terms of productivity what you eat is just as important as how fast you can prepare your meals and what time you choose to eat them. If you enjoy cooking or take a lot of pride in your food then you should plan for longer food
                                    preparation periods. However, learning to pre-prepare lunches and whip up quick and light breakfasts is a must.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    Eating until you are full is not ideal. You will suffer a lack of concentration and your productivity will also be marginally reduced. It is best to actually eat less. You will feel lighter on your feet and more focused.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    As a general guideline, breakfasts should include grains, fruit and yogurt, lunches should include, salads, vegetables and fruit, then dinner should include vegetables, grains and a source of protein. Try to eat 4 small meals per
                                    day.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">I personally eat granola, fruit and yogurt for breakfast, veggie pasta and banana for lunch with vegetable lasagne, stir fry, or roast with some meat for dinner.</span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">Drinking coffee is a choice and it can increase productivity so long as it is drank in moderation. Green tea can be equally effective.</span></p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <h2 class="ql-align-center"><span style="color: black; background-color: white;">3) BUILD A PRODUCTIVE ROUTINE</span></h2>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p class="ql-align-center">
                                <img src="~/Content/Images/pushupwoman1.jpg" />
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    Habit forming can be super effective for productivity. Your brain doesn’t mind working towards a reward. Habitual processes involve repetitive reward based actions.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    Good habits usually involve a delayed reward requiring a task to be completed beforehand. Bad habits involve instant gratification and can really ruin your performance and productivity.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    Any instant gratification habits such as smoking, or junk food, can be detrimental if they interfere with your working hours. During this time you brain is anticipating and working towards a longer term reward. The most productive
                                    people will make sure the only reward available requires the task to be completed.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p class="ql-align-center"><br /></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">When you begin working in the morning start by doing a To-Do list.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">Spend some time working out everything you need to do for the day. Estimate how long each item will take to complete and decide on the order of execution.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">Afterwards, imagine all the tasks are done before proceeding to tick them off as you go.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">Every time you complete a task take a break and do something else or do a different type of task.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><br /></p>
