                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    Working unnaturally hard will eventually lead to burn out. The level of productivity has to come naturally. You must not over work yourself. When you organise your daily tasks, make sure the amount of work you plan to do is
                                    realistic.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <span style="color: black; background-color: rgb(252, 252, 252);">
                                    You can boost productivity short term by drinking lots of coffee, or by staying up late, or fasting, or even by taking study drugs or nootropics. I do not really recommend them but if they are the routes you choose to take then make
                                    sure you do so responsibly and in a way that allows good recovery time.
                                </span>
                            </p>
                            <p><span>Slow and steady wins the race… but not too slow!!</span></p>
