                        <p><br /></p>
                        <p><b>There are many ways people try to go to sleep.</b> Most ways work with a similar underlying feature - <b>clear the mind</b>.</p>
                        <p><br /></p>
                        <blockquote class="quote" style="text-align:center;">Find a comfortable position, try not to move around, concentrate on the feelings in your body and allow yourself to become relaxed.</blockquote>
                        <p></p>
                        <p>As long as you are <b>feeling the sensations of your body</b>, you will be distracted from sounds, lights, and other conceptual, or distracting thoughts.</p>
                        <p><br /></p>
                        <p>Most people find <b>concentrating on the breath is effective</b> - Then, <i>when your mind is clear</i>, <b style="text-decoration:underline;">let go</b> of that concentration and just rest.</p>
                        <p><br /></p>
                        <p><b style="text-decoration:underline;">Do not <span>'wait'</span> to <span style="text-decoration:underline;">'fall asleep'</span></b>. There is<b style="text-decoration:underline;"> no moment</b> where your brain clicks into sleep mode, it is gradual.</p>
                        <p><br /></p>
                        <blockquote style="text-align:center;">Falling asleep is a <b>journey</b>, not an <b>event</b> waiting to happen.</blockquote>
