                            <h1>WHAT IS TRANSCENDENTAL MEDIATION?</h1>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <img src="~/Content/Images/TRANSCENDENTAL.jpg" />
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>Since the introduction of Buddhism, <b>meditation</b> has been adopted into almost <b>every contemporary philosophy and religion</b> in some form or another.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div style="padding:8px; border-radius:8px; border:1px dashed grey;background-color:rgba(255,221,0,0.05);">
                                <p>The central theme remains consistent: <br /><b>Concentration and focusing the mind on specific thoughts deliberately for a particular period of time.</b></p>
                            </div> <p><br /></p>
                            <p><b>Modern scientific skepticism cannot verify that which cannot be proven</b> or demonstrated to be the most likely truth, <b>when subject to scientific scrutiny</b>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                As with every era that humanity has struggled through, <i>the information and wisdom we have passed down through generations has been the <b>number one source of all knowledge</b>.</i>
                                Knowledge that the scientific community have found to be true, accounts for only a <b>tiny portion of human wisdom.</b>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                Although<i> breakthroughs have been made all over the scientific community regarding the benefits of meditation</i>, many religious or spiritually inclined individuals
                                will attest that <b>no 'scientifically-designed' medititative practice outperforms those of religious or spiritual practices.</b>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>The most widely utilised form of meditation, that is <i>most closely succesful in the face of scientific study</i>, is<b> Transcendental Meditation</b> - <i>but it is still a topic of debate as to whether this approach is one of 'science' or simply another 'spiritual practice'</i>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <blockquote>
                                The anecdotal claims are <b>insurmountable</b> and it is <b>common knowledge</b> that <b>Transcendental Meditation is most certainly effective</b>.
                            </blockquote>
                            <p></p>
                            <p>Transcendental Meditation is a simple form of meditation <b>introduced in the 1950s by Maharishi Mahesh Yogi</b>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div class="container" style="border:2px solid rgba(40,50,60,1);;padding:0;background-color:rgba(40,50,60,1);">
