                            <p>
                                <b>Most people’s brains are on autopilot for their entire life.</b> The actions, behaviors, habits, desires, reactions, ideas, goals,
                                aspirations, and everyday decisions, are <i>
                                    all accomplishments attributed to the uniquely advanced biological mechanism that is
                                    the brain.
                                </i>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                <b>If you are satisfied with <i style="text-decoration:underline;">being inside a body</i> with a powerful mind</b>,
                                so you can <i>sit back and experience life</i> and <i>watch everything play out</i> in the way your <b>brilliant brain choreographs it</b> – <i style="text-decoration:underline;">then that’s fine!</i>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>
                                However, <b style="background-color:rgba( 224, 255, 240,1); padding:2px;">
                                    your brain is one of the most easily manipulated and influence-driven objects
                                    in the entire world
                                </b>. <i>Your brain will lead you down the path of least resistance at all cost.</i>
                            </p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>This leaves your life in a state of <b>inadequate spiritual security</b>, where your <i>ideals and morals are subject to the influences of your experience and surroundings.</i></p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div style="background-color:rgba(255,221,82,0.05); border-radius:20px; padding:10px;border:1px dashed orange;text-align:center;">
                                <h5 style="text-align:left;">Ask Yourself These Questions:</h5>
                                <p><em style="color: rgb(132, 16, 14);"><br />What if <b>convenience</b> lets your life become <b>boring</b>? <br /></em></p>
                                <p><em style="color: rgb(132, 16, 14);"><br />What if <b>mass unethical social structures</b> become something you <b>actively participate in</b> for fear of resistance? </em></p>
                                <p><em style="color: rgb(132, 16, 14);"><br />What if something happens that <b>provokes a reaction from you that you’ll later regret</b>? </em></p>
                                <p><em style="color: rgb(132, 16, 14);"><br />What if you're <b>living your best life</b>, without ever discovering <b>you could have done so much more</b>?</em></p>
