                            <h2>8. Eat foods that clean your teeth</h2>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>A healthy habit that will surely push you down the path to a cleaner, healthier smile is <b>eating foods that target plaque and contribute to an overall reduction in acidity and bacterial populations</b> in your mouth.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><span style="background-color:yellow;"><b>The main three foods that are perfect for this job are as follows:</b></span></p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div style="border:1px solid rgba(40,50,60,0.05); background-color:rgba(100,100,100,0.05); padding:10px;">
                                <p>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;<b>Apples</b></p>
                                <p><br /></p>
                                <p>Apples are so abrasive to bite into. <b>They are loaded with firm fiber</b> that slides like super lowgrade sandpaper across the surface of your precious teeth, <b>gently removing any plaque and various other debris from all over your teeth</b>.</p>
                                <p><br /></p>
                                <p>Three things to keep in mind:</p>
                                <p><br /></p>
                                <ul>
                                    <li>To see the benefits of eating apples, eat them fairly often - <b>at least twice a week.</b></li>
                                    <li><b>Leave the skin on the apple</b> – it's perfect for your incisors to slice through and contains lots of nutritious fiber, vitamins, and minerals.</li>
                                    <li><b>Try to chew the apple with all the teeth in your mouth</b> to spread the benefit.</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div style="border:1px solid rgba(40,50,60,0.05); background-color:rgba(100,100,100,0.05); padding:10px;">
                                <p>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;<b>Carrots</b></p>
                                <p><br /></p>
                                <p>These have the same benefit as apples. <b>They are perfect when eaten raw</b>, for grinding away any bacterial or plaque residue on the surface of your teeth.</p>
                                <p><br /></p>
                                <p>Plus, eating raw carrots causes a <b>high level of salivation which is a great natural cleanser for your teeth</b>.</p>
                            </div>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <blockquote>In fact, any high-fiber food is great for your dental hygiene. High fiber foods are usually firm and provide a level of abrasion that is perfectly safe and effective for cleaning your teeth.</blockquote>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><i>Eating high fiber foods is a great substitute for when a toothbrush is hard to come by!</i></p>
