                            <h2><span class="fa fa-chevron-right">  </span>  Work Out A Meal Plan</h2>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>Planning what you will eat for a day is so important <b>if you want to be successful</b> in losing weight.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>If you don’t have a plan, then <b>there is a chance you will make the wrong decision</b> as a result of being unprepared when the time comes to eat.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>The plan needs to:<br /><br /></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Start<b> before you next go shopping</b>.</li>
                                <li>Contain meals that are <b>appetising, nourishing, and healthy</b>.</li>
                                <li>Account for the<b> minimum calorific intake</b> based on your activity level.</li>
                                <li>Represent a <b>permanent change in your relationship with food.</b></li>
                            </ul>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><b>There is no point in yo-yo dieting</b> unless you are looking for a quick-fix innefective solution. Yo-yo dieting encourages only temporary gains and minimal long term successes. <b>Don’t even bother</b>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><B>SO WHATS THE SECRET?</B></p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <blockquote style="text-align:center;">EAT MORE FIBRE</blockquote>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <img src="~/Content/Images/fibrediet.jpg" style="border:none;" />
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>Instead, decide to eat foods that are <b>healthy, sustainable, nourishing, and high in fibre</b>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><b>Fibre is a type of carbohydrate that cannot be digested by our bodies' enzymes.</b> It is incredibly healthy to eat lots of high-fibre foods because the fibre is a bulking agent.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p>Fibre carries the food you consume through the gastrointestinal system, providing mass which is <b>healthy for your gut</b>, while also <v>changing the way your body absorbs nutrients from your food</v>.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><b>Fibre allows nutrients to be absorbed over a longer period</b>, reducing blood sugar spikes that can prolong addictive tendencies.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <p><b>Fibre will also ‘fill you up’ and make your meals more substantial</b>. This means you can still eat lots of high-fibre foods since they are usually low in fat and calories.</p>
                            <p><br /></p>
                            <div style="width:100%;text-align:center;">
