                                    <h2>HOW DOES CONCENTRATION HYPNOSIS WORK?</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Concentration hypnosis requires a fixation upon an idea. For instance, you could repeat a sentence with a suggestive quality such as:</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <blockquote class="ql-align-center">“Every day, in every way, I’m getting better and better”</blockquote>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>During transcendental meditation, people usually focus and listen to the sound and sensation of the breath. This allows them to <strong>drain all the noise from their mind so they can think more clearly</strong>.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>During concentration hypnosis, thinking more clearly is not the goal</strong>. The goal is to increasingly embody the suggestive phrase, cumulatively, after multiple sessions.</p>
                                    <p>There are no overnight miracles!</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>The repetitive suggestion is not something to listen to while the noise drains away – instead, it is something to proactively repeat in your mind with utter focus.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>Your peripheral thoughts will be exploding with imagery and ideas</strong> as you keep activating the cortex with this meaningful suggestive phrase.</p>
