                                    <h2>1.&nbsp;IDENTIFY UNHEALTHY HABITS</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>The first step is to identify those areas of your life where your health falls short. Health can be physical, mental, or spiritual.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>
                                        <strong>Try to be specific in your judgement</strong>. It is not a good idea to try and change loads of things at once. You will see much greater results if you focus on one small issue at a time – otherwise, known as
                                        <strong>marginal adjustment.</strong>
                                    </p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>Marginal adjustment is the most effective method of self-improvement.</strong> The skill is to identify the small things that have the biggest influence.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <div style="border:5px solid rgba(40,50,60,1);">
                                        <div style="background-color:rgba(40,50,60,1); color:white;padding:5px;"><p style="color:white;"><strong>Some examples of marginal adjustments could include:</strong></p></div>
                                        <p><br /></p>
                                        <div style="padding:10px;">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li>Waking up earlier.</li>
                                                <li>Eating a healthy breakfast.</li>
                                                <li>Going for a short walk every evening.</li>
                                                <li>Eat 1 more piece of fruit every day.</li>
                                                <li>Workout for 10 minutes each morning.</li>
                                                <li>Write a to-do list each morning.</li>
                                                <li>Start meditating 10 minutes per day.</li>
                                                <li>Drink more water.</li>
                                            </ul>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p><strong>Think about the biggest health consequences that you face</strong> and determine what small changes you could make that would together eliminate that health consequence.</p>
                                    <p id="fourthb" style="margin-top:-50px;margin-bottom:100px;">
                                    </p>
                                    <h2>2.&nbsp;CHOOSE A HYPNOTIC SUGGESTION</h2>
                                    <p>
                                        <br />
                                    </p>
                                    <img src="~/Content/Images/a-decision-making-model-for-uncertainty.jpeg" />
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Whichever marginal adjustment you decide to act upon through self-hypnosis, you will need to come up with a hypnotic suggestion.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <div style="border:5px solid rgba(40,50,60,1);">
                                        <div style="background-color:rgba(40,50,60,1); color:white;padding:5px;"><p style="color:white;"><strong>Try to choose a phrase that is:</strong></p></div>
                                        <p><br /></p>
                                        <div style="padding:10px;">
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Specific</b></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>It should be clear how the suggestion is related to the adjustment you want it to achieve.</em></p>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Short</b></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>The suggestion should be a single sentence and preferably quite short. Shorter phrases are often more memorable. You will be repeating this phrase a lot so if it has a good ring to it then that’s a big advantage.</em></p>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Positive</b></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p><em>Avoid negative phrases, double negatives, and negative words. Try to frame every single word in its positive form. Say what you DO want, not what you DON’T want.</em></p>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <ul>
                                                <li><b>Realistic</b></li>
                                            </ul>
                                            <p><br /></p>
                                            <p>
                                                <em>
                                                    There is no point in trying to embody suggestions that are impossible or even ones that you think are impossible. Your brain will not fall for a trick like this. You know what's achievable, so don’t lie to yourself. If you do you
                                                    won't get anywhere with self-hypnosis.
                                                </em>
                                            </p>
                                        </div>
