                                    <h2>3.&nbsp;CHOOSE A TIME FRAME</h2>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <img src="~/Content/Images/tick-tock.gif" style="width:40%;" />
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>You should set out to improve a specific aspect of your health <strong>within a given time frame</strong>.</p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>If you ignore this step then you increase the chances of giving up. <strong>You need to see the light at the end of the tunnel. </strong></p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>A good time frame for something like this is one week. It is not long enough to form a solid habit but <strong>any longer could be overwhelming. </strong></p>
                                    <p><br /></p>
                                    <p>Every day you will have to <strong>abide by this single new rule</strong> and at the end of the week, you can decide whether to keep it up or not.</p>
