                <br>
            </p>
            <p><span style="color: black; background-color: white;">A healthy, plant-based diet aims to maximize the consumption of nutrient-dense plant foods while minimizing processed foods and animal foods, and products. It requires a higher consumption of vegetables, fruits, beans, peas, nuts, and seeds.</span></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><strong style="color: black; background-color: white;">What are the benefits of a whole-grain plant-based diet?</strong></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><span style="color: black; background-color: white;">A meta-analysis study (a study of 87 scientific studies) found that a whole-grain plant-based diet is effective for weight loss, and reducing the risk of heart disease and high blood pressure. </span></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><span style="color: black; background-color: white;">They also found that vegetarians' diets contained more nutrients and vegetarians were less nutrient deficient as a result. There was a correlation with a reduced rate of diabetes and heart disease. </span></p>

