            </p>
            <p>Sea birds, turtles, and marine mammals that happen to be near the long fishing lines can get unintentionally ensnared. The hooks can tear or even tear off fins, wings, and other body parts, killing the victims. Long-line fishing can also remove larger non-targeted ocean predators like dolphins.</p>
