            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Here are 8 steps that you need to take to change your relationship with food, maintain a healthy diet, and live longer and be healthier.</p>

            <p id="fourtha" style="margin-top:-50px;margin-bottom:100px;">
            </p>
            <H2>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;Consider what you shop for.</H2>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>When you make your shopping list, try to entirely skip the meat section as often as possible. Go straight to the fresh fruit and vegetable section and fill your basket with the essentials such as garlic, ginger, shallots, basil/thyme/sage/coriander, lettuce, onions, carrots, sweet potatoes, aubergines, kale, spinach, and a selection of fruit. </p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>From the cupboard foods section, you can pick up some tinned beans, peas, plum tomatoes, perhaps some raisins… and a selection of nuts, seeds, including almonds, walnuts, pecans, flaxseed, chia seeds, sesame seeds, and pumpkin seeds.</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>You should make sure you stock up on miso paste, nutritional yeast flakes, tamarind, brown rice, quinoa, and plain whole-grain oatmeal.</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Additionally, when you are at the till you should have zero plastic on the counter. This is usually possible if you stick to whole-grain plant-based foods.</p>

