            </H5>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>For lasagne, cut an aubergine in half, and boil with a quartered onion in a deep saucepan then simmer with the lid on for 20 minutes. Remove the lid, let the water boil away, and with a teaspoon of olive oil in the center, fry chopped garlic, ginger, basil, and thyme, before adding a tin of plum tomatoes, two cups of water, two tablespoons of nutritional yeast, and a cup of almonds. Boil for 20 minutes, then transfer to an oven tray, add some whole-grain lasagne sheets and bake for 20 minutes.</p>
