            <h2 class="ql-align-center">INGREDIENTS</h2>
            <p class="ql-align-center">
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>When you search for different supplements the first and most important factor to consider is the ingredients. Every supplement product page will provide the list of ingredients. It’s better to choose supplements with natural ingredients – they are usually safer, less invasive, and their action is usually less targeted and more balanced. There are a few other things to consider:</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><strong>Artificial Colours</strong></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Some supplements use artificial colours to make them more attractive for consuming. These are unnecessary additions to the ingredients list. Although the supplements may have natural colourings, at least they are not produced in a lab. Supplementation is an ongoing process where the results are discovered after a few weeks. Consuming artificial flavourings everyday is not ideal. </p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Try to ensure that your supplementation does not contain any artificial colours and the ingredients are 100% natural.</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><strong>Artificial Flavourings</strong></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Supplements are taken for a beneficial addition to your diet. It is unnecessary for them to be flavourful. More often than not, supplements that contain zero artificial flavours do not taste bad. For the same reasons as stated above, you should avoid artificial flavourings since they are unnecessary additions that accompany the ingredients you need.</p>
            <p>If you have supplements already that taste really nice, that wouldn’t be a factor when you choose to take one would it? Supplements are not sweets, so try to ensure they contain no artificial flavourings or sweeteners.</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p><strong>Genetically Modified Organisms</strong></p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
            <p>Many supplements on the market do contain natural ingredients, to an extent, but that doesn’t mean they are free of Genetically Modified Organisms, or GMO’s.</p>
            <p>
                <br>
            </p>
